title: Rules of Framing and Composition
description:
Motion Array Tutorials
262K subscribers
SUBSCRIBE
Check out some of our best looking footage! https://bit.ly/3cQ79iV 
And be sure to subscribe for more tips and tricks! 

Framing and composition are necessary terms to understand if you are going to make compelling visuals for your video.  These 7 rules for composition and framing will help you craft shots that look more and more professional.

In this video we explore a few of the more basic and foundational  rules of composition.  These include the rule of thirds, symmetry, leading lines, leading room, depth, and size of subject.  Lastly we look at how following these rules can help you, but strategically breaking them can also be an important decision that can benefit your project.  Ultimately, the most important part of film-making is your story.  Everything else comes second.
